---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<BaseLayout title="ASPSCR1-TFE3 Sarcoma Science" description="Understanding the precise molecular mechanisms driving alveolar soft part sarcoma through interactive visualization of translocation events and fusion proteins.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" rel="preconnect"/>
    <link crossorigin="" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" rel="preconnect"/>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
    <style>
        .chromosome-bar {
            transition: all 0.5s ease;
        }
        .chromosome-group:hover .chromosome-bar {
            transform: scaleY(1.1);
        }
    </style>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Fixed Background Layer -->
  <div class="fixed inset-0 z-0 pointer-events-none bg-ref-bg-light dark:bg-ref-bg-dark transition-colors duration-300">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(to_right,#80808012_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(to_bottom,#80808012_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:24px_24px]"></div>
      <div class="absolute left-0 right-0 top-0 -z-10 m-auto h-[500px] w-[500px] rounded-full bg-purple-500/20 opacity-50 blur-[100px]"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Scrollable Content Layer -->
  <div class="relative z-10 text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Header Section -->
    <header class="relative pt-6 pb-16 w-full">
        <div class="max-w-[90%] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight mb-6 leading-tight">
                The Science Behind <br class="hidden md:block"/>
                <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-ref-primary to-indigo-600 dark:from-purple-400 dark:to-indigo-400">
                    ASPSCR1-TFE3 Sarcoma
                </span>
            </h1>
            <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                Understanding the precise molecular mechanisms driving alveolar soft part sarcoma through interactive visualization of translocation events and fusion proteins.
            </p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="max-w-[85%] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pb-24 space-y-16">
        <!-- Mechanism Section -->
        <section class="relative group">
            <div class="absolute -inset-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-indigo-50 dark:from-slate-800/50 dark:to-slate-900/50 rounded-[2.5rem] -z-10 opacity-50 blur-xl transition duration-500 group-hover:opacity-100"></div>
            <div class="bg-ref-surface-light dark:bg-ref-surface-dark rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-12 items-start">
                    <div class="flex-1">
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                            <div class="p-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/50 rounded-lg text-ref-primary">
                                <Icon name="mdi:shuffle" class="w-6 h-6" />
                            </div>
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">The Mechanism</h2>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ref-primary mb-4">The Translocation t(X;17)(p11;q25)</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                            At the heart of alveolar soft part sarcoma (ASPS) lies a precise chromosomal rearrangement. This translocation breaks two chromosomes—the X chromosome and chromosome 17—at specific locations and exchanges their genetic material.
                        </p>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900/50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-700">
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">The Molecular Event</h4>
                            <ul class="space-y-3">
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 mt-1.5 rounded-full bg-indigo-500 flex-shrink-0"></span>
                                    <span>The <strong>ASPSCR1 gene</strong> (chromosome 17) breaks at position q25.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 mt-1.5 rounded-full bg-pink-500 flex-shrink-0"></span>
                                    <span>The <strong>TFE3 gene</strong> (X chromosome) breaks at position p11.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 mt-1.5 rounded-full bg-ref-primary flex-shrink-0"></span>
                                    <span>These fragments recombine, creating the <strong>fusion protein ASPSCR1-TFE3</strong>.</span>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 italic">
                            Found in virtually 100% of ASPS cases, this breakpoint occurs in-frame, producing a functional, aberrant protein.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Visualization -->
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-6 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-700 chromosome-group">
                        <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 mb-6 uppercase">Translocation Visualization</div>
                        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 md:gap-8">
                            <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
                                <div class="w-4 h-20 bg-pink-200 dark:bg-pink-900 rounded-t-full relative overflow-hidden chromosome-bar">
                                    <div class="absolute bottom-0 w-full h-8 bg-pink-500"></div> 
                                </div>
                                <div class="w-4 h-12 bg-pink-200 dark:bg-pink-900 rounded-b-full chromosome-bar"></div>
                                <span class="text-xs font-bold text-pink-600 dark:text-pink-400 mt-2">Chr X</span>
                            </div>
                            <Icon name="mdi:plus" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-300 dark:text-slate-600" />
                            <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
                                <div class="w-4 h-12 bg-indigo-200 dark:bg-indigo-900 rounded-t-full chromosome-bar"></div>
                                <div class="w-4 h-20 bg-indigo-200 dark:bg-indigo-900 rounded-b-full relative overflow-hidden chromosome-bar">
                                    <div class="absolute top-0 w-full h-8 bg-indigo-500"></div> 
                                </div>
                                <span class="text-xs font-bold text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 mt-2">Chr 17</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="my-6">
                            <Icon name="mdi:arrow-down" class="w-8 h-8 text-ref-primary animate-bounce" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2 p-4 bg-white dark:bg-black rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-purple-100 dark:border-purple-900 w-full">
                            <div class="flex flex-col items-center w-full">
                                <div class="w-6 h-32 relative rounded-full overflow-hidden shadow-md ring-2 ring-ref-primary ring-offset-2 dark:ring-offset-black">
                                    <div class="absolute top-0 w-full h-1/2 bg-indigo-500 flex items-center justify-center">
                                        <span class="text-[10px] text-white font-bold rotate-90 opacity-80">ASPSCR1</span>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="absolute bottom-0 w-full h-1/2 bg-pink-500 flex items-center justify-center">
                                        <span class="text-[10px] text-white font-bold rotate-90 opacity-80">TFE3</span>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="text-sm font-bold text-ref-primary mt-3">Oncogenic Fusion</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Target Section -->
        <section>
            <div class="text-center mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">The Target: ASPSCR1-TFE3 Fusion Protein</h2>
                <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    A constitutively active transcription factor—a master regulator of gene expression gone awry.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="group bg-ref-surface-light dark:bg-ref-surface-dark rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 hover:border-ref-primary/50 transition-all hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-indigo-100 dark:bg-indigo-900/20 rounded-bl-[4rem] -mr-8 -mt-8 z-0 transition-transform group-hover:scale-110"></div>
                    <div class="relative z-10">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-indigo-100 dark:bg-indigo-900/50 text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
                            <Icon name="mdi:dns" class="w-6 h-6 text-2xl" />
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Why It's a Transcription Factor</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-4">
                            <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                                <Icon name="mdi:check-circle-outline" class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-500 text-lg" />
                                <span><strong>TFE3</strong> contributes its DNA binding domain, attaching to specific sequences.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                                <Icon name="mdi:check-circle-outline" class="w-5 h-5 text-indigo-500 text-lg" />
                                <span><strong>ASPSCR1</strong> contributes activation domains that turn on target genes.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/30 p-3 rounded-lg text-sm text-indigo-800 dark:text-indigo-200 font-medium">
                                Result: A protein that is always "on", constantly activating genes.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="group bg-ref-surface-light dark:bg-ref-surface-dark rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 hover:border-pink-500/50 transition-all hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/20 rounded-bl-[4rem] -mr-8 -mt-8 z-0 transition-transform group-hover:scale-110"></div>
                    <div class="relative z-10">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/50 text-pink-600 dark:text-pink-400 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
                            <Icon name="mdi:water" class="w-6 h-6 text-2xl" />
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Driving Angiogenesis</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-4">
                            <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                                <Icon name="mdi:trending-up" class="w-5 h-5 text-pink-500 text-lg" />
                                <span>Activates <strong>angiogenic pathways</strong> creating new blood vessels.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                                <Icon name="mdi:trending-up" class="w-5 h-5 text-pink-500 text-lg" />
                                <span>Upregulates <strong>VEGF</strong> and related signaling molecules.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="bg-pink-50 dark:bg-pink-900/30 p-3 rounded-lg text-sm text-pink-800 dark:text-pink-200 font-medium">
                                Result: Tumor cells hyperdependent on new blood vessel formation.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-8 text-center text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 italic max-w-3xl mx-auto border-l-4 border-ref-primary pl-4">
                "Unlike normal TFE3, which is tightly regulated, the fusion bypasses all checkpoints. This unrelenting activation offers potential therapeutic opportunities."
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Unique Section -->
        <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-100 to-slate-200 dark:from-slate-800 dark:to-slate-900 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Why It's Unique</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-10">Resistance & Vascularization Dependence</p>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400 flex items-center justify-center">
                            <Icon name="mdi:shield" class="w-8 h-8 text-3xl" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">1. Intrinsic Chemotherapy Resistance</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4">
                            Traditional chemo works by inducing DNA damage. ASPSCR1-TFE3 sarcoma cells are remarkably resistant because:
                        </p>
                        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-700/50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600">
                                <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">Enhanced Repair</h4>
                                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Upregulates genes that repair DNA damage quickly.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-700/50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600">
                                <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">Altered Metabolism</h4>
                                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Metabolic reprogramming reduces dependence on standard signals.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-700/50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-600">
                                <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">Survival Pathways</h4>
                                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Anti-apoptotic pathways protect tumor cells from death.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
                    <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex items-center justify-center">
                            <Icon name="mdi:hospital-box" class="w-8 h-8 text-3xl" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">2. Extreme Angiogenesis Dependence</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4">
                            This is one of the most vascularized soft tissue sarcomas known.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2">
                            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-700/30 p-2 rounded">
                                <Icon name="mdi:arrow-right" class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 text-sm" />
                                <span><strong>Tumor growth bottleneck:</strong> Cannot grow > few millimeters without new blood vessels.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-700/30 p-2 rounded">
                                <Icon name="mdi:arrow-right" class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 text-sm" />
                                <span><strong>Therapeutic opportunity:</strong> Targeting VEGF or TFE3 may be more effective than chemo.</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-8 bg-ref-primary/10 dark:bg-ref-primary/20 border border-ref-primary/20 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
                <p class="text-ref-primary-dark dark:text-purple-300 font-medium">
                    In summary, this biology opens new therapeutic avenues: instead of trying to poison the tumor with drugs it can resist, we can starve it by cutting off its blood supply, or directly inhibit the fusion protein itself.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
  </div>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "page": "The Science",
    "disease": "Alveolar Soft Part Sarcoma",
    "driver": "ASPSCR1–TFE3 fusion",
    "mechanisms": ["angiogenesis dependency", "TFE3-driven transcription"],
    "therapeutic_vulnerabilities": ["VEGF pathway", "MET signaling"],
    "current_therapies": ["atezolizumab", "pazopanib"],
    "research_focus": ["target discovery", "computational modeling"]
  }
  </script>
</BaseLayout>